FBIS4-42356 "drweu106_l_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 SPAIN `Terrorist' Attacks Reported in Madrid 1 Jun `Terrorist' Attacks Reported in Madrid 1 Jun Army General Dies PA0106123694 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0741 GMT 1 Jun 94 PA0106123694 Madrid EFE Spanish BFN [Excerpt] Madrid, 1 Jun (EFE) -- Four shots fired by a man and woman ended the life Army Brigadier General Juan Jose Hernandez Rovira, the victim of a terrorist attack carried out in Madrid today. The attack took place at 0845 (0645 GMT) as the general was leaving his home, located in a Salamanca neighborhood in the center of Madrid. A resident of a building near the site of the attack told EFE the general, the father of six children, lost his wife last year. Municipal police sources told EFE that the general, who was still alive after the shooting, was taken to a hospital but died on arrival. [passage omitted]
